@startuml BankApplication_Annotated

skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0
skinparam nodesep 35
skinparam ranksep 30
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

skinparam class {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam enum {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

skinparam interface {
    BackgroundColor #2ECC71
    BorderColor #1A1A1A
    FontColor White
    FontSize 10
}

title <size:18>Bank Application - Class Diagram (Annotated for Interview)</size>\n<size:11>Trace: "Customer opens account, deposits money, transfers to another account, transaction logged, notifications sent."</size>


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 1: FACADE
' ====================================================================
class BankingService <<Facade>> {
    - accounts : Map<String, Account>
    - customers : Map<String, Customer>
    - transactionService : TransactionService
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    - interestService : InterestService
    - auditLog : AuditLog
    --
    + openAccount(customer, type, deposit) : Account
    + closeAccount(accountId) : void
    + deposit(accountId, amount) : Transaction
    + withdraw(accountId, amount) : Transaction
    + transfer(fromId, toId, amount) : Transaction
    + getBalance(accountId) : double
    + getStatement(accountId, from, to) : List<Transaction>
    + applyInterest(accountId) : void
}

note top of BankingService #BBDEFB
    **STEP 1 - Start here.**
    "Customer walks into a bank (or opens
    the app). BankingService is the **Facade**
    — single API for account management,
    deposits, withdrawals, transfers, and
    statements. Hides all internal services."
    **Pattern: Facade | SRP, DIP**
end note


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 2: CUSTOMER MODEL
' ====================================================================
class Customer {
    - customerId : String
    - name : String
    - email : String
    - phone : String
    - address : Address
    - kycStatus : KYCStatus
    - accounts : List<Account>
    --
    + isVerified() : boolean
    + getAccounts() : List<Account>
}

class Address {
    - street : String
    - city : String
    - state : String
    - zipCode : String
    - country : String
}

enum KYCStatus {
    PENDING
    VERIFIED
    REJECTED
    EXPIRED
}

note top of Customer #C8E6C9
    **STEP 2 - Who is the customer?**
    "Customer has name, contact, address,
    KYC status. Must be VERIFIED before
    opening accounts. One customer can
    have multiple accounts (savings,
    current, fixed deposit)."
end note

Customer *-- Address
Customer --> KYCStatus
BankingService --> Customer : manages >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 3: ACCOUNT HIERARCHY — Factory Method
' ====================================================================
abstract class Account {
    - accountId : String
    - accountNumber : String
    - customer : Customer
    - balance : double
    - status : AccountStatus
    - type : AccountType
    - createdAt : LocalDateTime
    - observers : List<AccountObserver>
    --
    + deposit(amount) : void
    + withdraw(amount) : void
    + getBalance() : double
    + {abstract} getInterestRate() : double
    + {abstract} getMinBalance() : double
    + {abstract} getWithdrawalLimit() : double
    + registerObserver(obs) : void
    + notifyObservers(event) : void
}

class SavingsAccount {
    - interestRate : double
    - minBalance : double
    - monthlyWithdrawalLimit : int
    - withdrawalsThisMonth : int
    --
    + getInterestRate() : double
    + getMinBalance() : double
    + getWithdrawalLimit() : double
    + canWithdraw() : boolean
}

class CurrentAccount {
    - overdraftLimit : double
    --
    + getInterestRate() : double
    + getMinBalance() : double
    + getWithdrawalLimit() : double
    + getAvailableBalance() : double
}

class FixedDepositAccount {
    - principal : double
    - interestRate : double
    - maturityDate : LocalDate
    - termMonths : int
    - penaltyPercent : double
    --
    + getInterestRate() : double
    + getMinBalance() : double
    + getWithdrawalLimit() : double
    + isMatured() : boolean
    + getMaturityAmount() : double
    + prematureWithdrawalPenalty() : double
}

enum AccountType {
    SAVINGS
    CURRENT
    FIXED_DEPOSIT
    RECURRING_DEPOSIT
}

enum AccountStatus {
    ACTIVE
    FROZEN
    CLOSED
    DORMANT
}

note top of Account #FFE0B2
    **STEP 3 - Account hierarchy.**
    "Abstract **Account** defines the contract.
    Concrete types have different rules:
    **Savings**: interest rate, min balance,
    monthly withdrawal limit.
    **Current**: overdraft, no interest.
    **FixedDeposit**: locked term, penalty
    for early withdrawal."

    "Each type overrides getInterestRate(),
    getMinBalance(), getWithdrawalLimit().
    **Factory** creates the right subclass."
    **Pattern: Factory Method | OCP, LSP**
end note

Account <|-- SavingsAccount
Account <|-- CurrentAccount
Account <|-- FixedDepositAccount
Account --> AccountType
Account --> AccountStatus
Account --> Customer : owned by >


class AccountFactory <<Factory>> {
    --
    + {static} createAccount(type, customer, deposit) : Account
}

note bottom of AccountFactory #FFE0B2
    **Factory Method.**
    "AccountFactory.createAccount(SAVINGS, cust, 5000)
    returns a SavingsAccount with correct rules.
    Add RecurringDeposit? One new class + one
    factory case. Client code unchanged."
    **Pattern: Factory | OCP**
end note

AccountFactory --> Account : creates >
BankingService --> AccountFactory : uses >


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 4: TRANSACTION + COMMAND PATTERN
' ====================================================================
class Transaction {
    - transactionId : String
    - type : TransactionType
    - amount : double
    - fromAccount : Account
    - toAccount : Account
    - timestamp : LocalDateTime
    - status : TransactionStatus
    - description : String
    - referenceNumber : String
    --
    + isSuccessful() : boolean
    + getAmount() : double
}

enum TransactionType {
    DEPOSIT
    WITHDRAWAL
    TRANSFER
    INTEREST_CREDIT
    PENALTY_DEBIT
    FEE
}

enum TransactionStatus {
    PENDING
    COMPLETED
    FAILED
    REVERSED
}

interface TransactionCommand <<Command>> {
    + execute() : Transaction
    + undo() : Transaction
    + validate() : boolean
}

class DepositCommand {
    - account : Account
    - amount : double
    --
    + execute() : Transaction
    + undo() : Transaction
    + validate() : boolean
}

class WithdrawCommand {
    - account : Account
    - amount : double
    --
    + execute() : Transaction
    + undo() : Transaction
    + validate() : boolean
}

class TransferCommand {
    - fromAccount : Account
    - toAccount : Account
    - amount : double
    --
    + execute() : Transaction
    + undo() : Transaction
    + validate() : boolean
}

note top of TransactionCommand #FFCDD2
    **STEP 4 - Deposit / Withdraw / Transfer.**
    "Each operation is a **Command** object.
    Why? Commands can be **validated** before
    execution, **undone** (reversal), **logged**
    (audit trail), and **queued** (batch)."

    "DepositCommand: add to balance.
    WithdrawCommand: check limit, deduct.
    TransferCommand: withdraw from A + deposit to B
    atomically. undo() reverses the operation."
    **Pattern: Command | SRP, OCP**
end note

TransactionCommand <|.. DepositCommand
TransactionCommand <|.. WithdrawCommand
TransactionCommand <|.. TransferCommand
TransactionCommand --> Transaction : produces >
Transaction --> TransactionType
Transaction --> TransactionStatus


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 5: TRANSACTION SERVICE — Executor
' ====================================================================
class TransactionService {
    - validators : List<TransactionValidator>
    - auditLog : AuditLog
    --
    + executeTransaction(command) : Transaction
    + reverseTransaction(transactionId) : Transaction
    + getHistory(accountId, from, to) : List<Transaction>
}

interface TransactionValidator <<Strategy>> {
    + validate(command) : ValidationResult
}

class BalanceValidator {
    + validate(command) : ValidationResult
}

class DailyLimitValidator {
    - dailyLimit : double
    --
    + validate(command) : ValidationResult
}

class FraudDetectionValidator {
    - maxSingleTransaction : double
    --
    + validate(command) : ValidationResult
}

class AccountStatusValidator {
    + validate(command) : ValidationResult
}

class ValidationResult {
    - valid : boolean
    - errorMessage : String
}

note bottom of TransactionValidator #FFCDD2
    **STEP 5 - Validate before executing.**
    "**Strategy Pattern** — validation rules
    are pluggable. Checked in sequence:"

    "1. **AccountStatusValidator**: is account active?
    2. **BalanceValidator**: sufficient funds?
    3. **DailyLimitValidator**: within daily cap?
    4. **FraudDetectionValidator**: suspicious amount?"

    "All must pass. Add KYCValidator? One class.
    Chain of validators, each independent."
    **Pattern: Strategy (Chain) | OCP, SRP**
end note

TransactionValidator <|.. BalanceValidator
TransactionValidator <|.. DailyLimitValidator
TransactionValidator <|.. FraudDetectionValidator
TransactionValidator <|.. AccountStatusValidator
TransactionService o--> TransactionValidator : validates with >
TransactionService --> TransactionCommand : executes >
TransactionValidator --> ValidationResult
BankingService --> TransactionService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 6: INTEREST CALCULATION — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface InterestStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + calculateInterest(account, days) : double
}

class SimpleInterestStrategy {
    + calculateInterest(account, days) : double
}

class CompoundInterestStrategy {
    - compoundingFrequency : int
    --
    + calculateInterest(account, days) : double
}

class TieredInterestStrategy {
    - tiers : List<InterestTier>
    --
    + calculateInterest(account, days) : double
}

class InterestTier {
    - minBalance : double
    - maxBalance : double
    - rate : double
}

class InterestService {
    - strategyMap : Map<AccountType, InterestStrategy>
    --
    + calculateInterest(account) : double
    + applyInterest(account) : Transaction
    + setStrategy(type, strategy) : void
}

note bottom of InterestStrategy #D1C4E9
    **STEP 6 - Interest calculation.**
    "Different accounts earn interest differently.
    **Strategy Pattern:**
    **SimpleInterest**: P * R * T / 100 (Savings).
    **CompoundInterest**: quarterly compounding (FD).
    **TieredInterest**: higher rate for higher balance."

    "InterestService maps AccountType to Strategy.
    Savings -> Simple, FD -> Compound.
    Change Savings to Tiered? Swap one mapping."
    **Pattern: Strategy | OCP, DIP**
end note

InterestStrategy <|.. SimpleInterestStrategy
InterestStrategy <|.. CompoundInterestStrategy
InterestStrategy <|.. TieredInterestStrategy
TieredInterestStrategy o--> InterestTier
InterestService --> InterestStrategy : delegates >
BankingService --> InterestService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 7: OBSERVER — Notifications + Audit
' ====================================================================
interface AccountObserver <<Observer>> {
    + onAccountEvent(account, event) : void
}

class TransactionAlertObserver {
    - notificationService : NotificationService
    --
    + onAccountEvent(account, event) : void
}

class LowBalanceObserver {
    - threshold : double
    --
    + onAccountEvent(account, event) : void
}

class FraudAlertObserver {
    --
    + onAccountEvent(account, event) : void
}

class AuditLogObserver {
    - auditLog : AuditLog
    --
    + onAccountEvent(account, event) : void
}

class AuditLog {
    - entries : List<AuditEntry>
    --
    + log(entry) : void
    + getEntries(accountId, from, to) : List<AuditEntry>
}

class AuditEntry {
    - timestamp : LocalDateTime
    - accountId : String
    - action : String
    - performedBy : String
    - details : String
}

note bottom of AccountObserver #B2EBF2
    **STEP 7 - Everyone gets notified.**
    "On every transaction/account event,
    Account calls notifyObservers().
    **Observer Pattern**:"

    "**TransactionAlert**: 'Rs 5000 debited'.
    **LowBalanceObserver**: warns if below threshold.
    **FraudAlertObserver**: flags suspicious activity.
    **AuditLogObserver**: logs every action for
    compliance (RBI/regulatory requirement)."
    **Pattern: Observer | OCP, SRP**
end note

AccountObserver <|.. TransactionAlertObserver
AccountObserver <|.. LowBalanceObserver
AccountObserver <|.. FraudAlertObserver
AccountObserver <|.. AuditLogObserver
Account --> AccountObserver : notifies >
AuditLogObserver --> AuditLog : writes to >
AuditLog *-- AuditEntry
BankingService --> AuditLog


' ====================================================================
'  NOTIFICATION — Strategy Pattern
' ====================================================================
class NotificationService {
    - strategies : List<NotificationStrategy>
    --
    + notify(customer, message) : void
}

interface NotificationStrategy <<Strategy>> {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class EmailNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class SMSNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

class PushNotification {
    + send(recipient, message) : void
}

NotificationStrategy <|.. EmailNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. SMSNotification
NotificationStrategy <|.. PushNotification
NotificationService --> NotificationStrategy : delegates >
TransactionAlertObserver --> NotificationService : uses >
BankingService --> NotificationService


' ====================================================================
'  STEP 8: ACCOUNT STATE — State Pattern
' ====================================================================
interface AccountState <<State>> {
    + deposit(account, amount) : void
    + withdraw(account, amount) : void
    + freeze(account) : void
    + close(account) : void
    + activate(account) : void
}

class ActiveState {
    + deposit(account, amount) : void
    + withdraw(account, amount) : void
    + freeze(account) : void
    + close(account) : void
}

class FrozenState {
    + deposit(account, amount) : void
    + activate(account) : void
    + close(account) : void
}

class DormantState {
    + deposit(account, amount) : void
    + activate(account) : void
    + close(account) : void
}

class ClosedState {
    ' terminal
}

note bottom of AccountState #FFCDD2
    **STEP 8 - Account lifecycle.**
    "**State Pattern** — accounts have states too.
    **Active**: can deposit, withdraw, freeze, close.
    **Frozen**: can only deposit (court order/fraud).
    **Dormant**: inactive 2+ years, can reactivate.
    **Closed**: terminal."

    "FrozenState.withdraw() throws error.
    No if-else in Account. Each state
    enforces its own rules."
    Active -> Frozen -> Active
    Active -> Dormant -> Active
    Active/Dormant -> Closed
    **Pattern: State | SRP, OCP**
end note

AccountState <|.. ActiveState
AccountState <|.. FrozenState
AccountState <|.. DormantState
AccountState <|.. ClosedState
Account --> AccountState : delegates >


' ====================================================================
'  WRAP UP
' ====================================================================
note as WRAPUP #FFFDE7
    **WRAP UP:** "Customer opens account via **Factory** (Savings/Current/FD).
    Deposits money via **DepositCommand** (**Command Pattern**). Transfers to
    friend via **TransferCommand** — validated by chained validators
    (**Strategy**). Transaction logged by **AuditLogObserver**, customer
    alerted by **TransactionAlertObserver** (**Observer**). Interest calculated
    by **InterestStrategy** (Simple/Compound/Tiered). Account lifecycle
    managed by **State Pattern** (Active/Frozen/Dormant/Closed).
    7 patterns: **Facade, Factory, Command, Strategy (x3), State, Observer**."
end note


' ====================================================================
'  LEGEND
' ====================================================================
legend bottom
    |= Step |= What Happens |= Pattern |= SOLID |
    | 1 | Customer calls BankingService (deposit/withdraw/transfer) | Facade | SRP, DIP |
    | 2 | Customer with KYC, address, multiple accounts | -- | SRP |
    | 3 | Account hierarchy: Savings / Current / FixedDeposit | Factory Method | OCP, LSP |
    | 4 | Each operation is a Command: execute(), undo(), validate() | Command | SRP, OCP |
    | 5 | Validators: balance, daily limit, fraud, account status | Strategy (chain) | OCP, SRP |
    | 6 | Interest: simple / compound / tiered per account type | Strategy | OCP, DIP |
    | 7 | Transaction alert, low balance, fraud alert, audit log | Observer + Strategy | OCP, SRP |
    | 8 | Account: Active -> Frozen -> Dormant -> Closed | State | SRP, OCP |
    |  |  |  |  |
    | **Account Mgmt** = Steps 2-3,8 | **Transactions** = Steps 4-5 | **Interest + Notify** = Steps 6-7 |  |
endlegend

@enduml
